Update classifiers in setup.py

- Specify that we support Python 2 and 3.
- Use newish `Framework :: Robot Framework` classifier

Explicitly make print function.

PR #4 already changed usage to `print()`. Fixes #3.

Merge pull request #4 from vkruoso/py3

Python 3 compatibility

Merge pull request #2 from vkruoso/master

Exposing `ERROR` log level

Fixed some Python style

Signed-off-by: Vinicius Kwiecien Ruoso <vinicius.ruoso@gmail.com>

Added support for messages on error level

The error log level was exposed to RobotFramework logging API in 2.9.
The related issue is robotframework/robotframework#1916.
